President Obama has announced his intention to appoint Bruce Cole as a member of the Dwight D. Eisenhower Memorial Commission. Bruce Cole is currently a Senior Fellow at the Ethics and Public Policy Center, and has previously held positions at the Hudson Institute and the American Revolution Center. He served as Chairman of the National Endowment of the Humanities from 2001 to 2009 and is a former Professor of Art History and Comparative Literature at Indiana University. Bruce Cole has also received the Presidential Citizens Medal in 2008. He holds a B.A. from Case Western Reserve University, an M.A. from Oberlin College, and a Ph.D. from Bryn Mawr College.